      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TUXEDO MISS (7) was an overdue maiden winner at Echuca by a nose nearly 3 weeks ago, and this field is not much tougher. She is deep into her prep, and now that the penny has dropped, she can repeat the dose. BREAK THE TABOO (4) hardly runs a bad race, and has no trouble with wet ground, and she can produce her usual honest effort. Stick with her. PORT LOUIS (1) may not have coped with a 9-day backup at Geelong in a tougher field than this, and it is a run best forgotten. He had won 2 races on the bounce prior to that, and he is capable of bouncing straight back into the money here. PRINCE SONIC (2) rises in trip second up, and he is expected to be more competitive this time. Include in all top 4 combos to be safe. TALLAPOOSA (5) is hard to catch, and will be over 5 weeks between runs leading into this assignment. Don't drop her in this field.",
